### TEMPLATES TO CREATE (4 new)

All templates located in: `src/app/blog/[slug]/templates/`

**Common end section order (all templates):**
1. Remaining content
2. `<AboutEEAT />`
3. `<FinalNewsletter />`
4. `<ReadMoreSection />`

**1. CenterTemplate.tsx**
- Hero: Full-width centered image (natural aspect ratio, no crop/fill)
- Title/meta: Centered below hero
- Content: Centered column (max-width from config)
- Manual component placement in template code

**2. SplitLeftTemplate.tsx**
- Desktop: 50/50 split hero section
  - Left: Hero image (object-fit: contain, vertically & horizontally centered)
  - Right: Title/meta (vertically & horizontally centered)
- Mobile: Stacked - hero image (centered with padding), then title/meta
- Content: Centered column below
- Manual component placement

**3. SplitRightTemplate.tsx**
- Desktop: 50/50 split hero section
  - Left: Title/meta (vertically & horizontally centered)
  - Right: Hero image (object-fit: contain, vertically & horizontally centered)
- Mobile: Stacked - hero image (centered with padding), then title/meta
- Content: Centered column below
- Manual component placement

**4. GridTemplate.tsx**
- Title/meta: Centered, ABOVE hero grid
- Hero: 4 images in 2x2 grid (desktop), fixed aspect ratio (3:4 or 4:5), object-fit: cover
- Mobile: Title/meta at top, then middle 2 images only (stacked vertically)
- Content: Centered column below
- Props: `heroImages: string[]` (4 images)
- Manual component placement

### MOBILE SPECIFICATIONS
- Editorial padding: `24px` or `32px` sides
- Images in split templates: Centered with padding, not full-width
- All text: Properly sized for mobile (check config)
- Grid template: Show only middle 2 of 4 images on mobile

### FILES TO MODIFY

**1. src/app/blog/[slug]/page.tsx**
```typescript
// Add template switching logic
import CenterTemplate from './templates/CenterTemplate'
import SplitLeftTemplate from './templates/SplitLeftTemplate'
import SplitRightTemplate from './templates/SplitRightTemplate'
import GridTemplate from './templates/GridTemplate'

const templates = {
  'center': CenterTemplate,
  'split-left': SplitLeftTemplate,
  'split-right': SplitRightTemplate,
  'grid': GridTemplate
}

const Template = templates[post.template] || BlogPost // Fallback to existing
return <Template post={post} />
```

